

=Description=

"The wiki-based CIRN Commons is to be one of the main resources of the CIRN community, next to the annual Prato conference and the Journal of Community Informatics. It is the successor to the ciresearch.net site, and should contain a dynamic knowledge repository necessary for Community Informatics research and practice to be done more effectively and efficiently. Basically, anything that any community member things relevant for somebody in the community is relevant. Check out the announcement about the launch for more background. As our community grows, its set of knowledge resources will grow as well. Using this wiki as its main tool, we can ensure that the workload and ownership of the commons is distributed fairly."
(http://cirn.wikispaces.com/About)


